The current monetary policy is appropriate;
The current policy helps the Fed reach its two goals (maximum employment and stable prices);
Inflation is still above the 2% target;
In 2025, the US economy grew steadily and entered 2026 in good shape;
The negative effects of the government shutdown should fade during this quarter;
Powell refused to say whether he will stay at the Fed after his term as chair ends;
Powell noted that the Fed usually does not comment on the US dollar;
Most of the extra inflation comes from tariffs;
No decisions have been made about future meetings;
The impact of tariffs on prices is expected to peak this year and then decline. If this trend is confirmed, it would support moving toward easier monetary policy;
Consumer spending remains stable, and business investment keeps growing;
Powell is confident that the Fed will remain independent and sees no signs of losing that independence;
US government debt of $38.5 trillion is ‚Äúnot sustainable‚Äù;
Raising interest rates is not the main scenario;
The economy has once again surprised with its strength;
There is no need to pay too much attention to the rise in gold prices;
Powell said he would advise the next Fed chair to stay away from politics and earn the trust of Congress.

